%spark.pyspark

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

import datetime
from pyspark.sql.functions import when
from pyspark.sql.functions import to_date, date_format

paragraphs.title: Uploading dataset
paragraphs.text:
%sh
wget -P dataset https://www.dropbox.com/s/zc3tdpb7tjj4nt1/dataset-bikesharing.csv

%sh
hdfs dfs -ls dataset

paragraphs.title: Read dataset
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
df_dataset = spark.read.csv(path='hdfs://192.168.56.103/user/yava/dataset/dataset-bikesharing.csv', header = True, inferSchema = True)
df_dataset.show(5)
df_dataset.printSchema()

%spark.pyspark
print ('Number of records: %d ' % df_dataset.count())

%spark.pyspark
df_dataset.groupBy() \
           .agg({'*' : 'count', 'cnt' : 'sum'} ) \
           .toDF('total_trx', 'num_row') \
           .show()

paragraphs.title: Average Usage per hour
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
df_agg_hourly = df_dataset.groupBy('hr') \
                          .agg({'cnt' : 'avg'}) \
                          .orderBy('hr') \
                          .toDF('hour_id', 'avg_shared')
df_agg_hourly.show(5)

%spark.pyspark
pd_agg_hourly = df_agg_hourly.toPandas()
pd_agg_hourly.head()

%spark.pyspark
sns.catplot(data=pd_agg_hourly, x="hour_id", y="avg_shared", 
            kind="bar",             # Options are: “point”, “bar”, “strip”, “swarm”, “box”, “violin”, or “boxen”
            palette="ch:.25",  
            height=5,              # Make the plot 10 units high
            aspect=2
            ) \
            .set( \
                 xlabel= 'Hour of Day', \
                 ylabel= 'Average Number of BikeShares', \
                 title = 'Average BikeShares - Hourly')

paragraphs.title: Average usage pe dar
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
from pyspark.sql.functions import to_date, date_format

pd_agg_daily = df_dataset.select("dteday", "weekday", "cnt") \
          .withColumn('day_name', date_format(df_dataset.dteday, 'E')) \
          .groupBy("weekday", "day_name") \
          .agg({ '*' : 'count', 'cnt' : 'avg'}) \
          .orderBy("weekday") \
          .toDF('weekday', 'day_name', 'avg_bikeshares', 'num_record') \
          .select('day_name', 'avg_bikeshares') \
          .toPandas()

pd_agg_daily.head(7)

%spark.pyspark
sns.catplot(data=pd_agg_daily, x="day_name", y="avg_bikeshares", 
            kind="bar",             # Options are: “point”, “bar”, “strip”, “swarm”, “box”, “violin”, or “boxen”
            palette="ch:.25",  
            height=5,              # Make the plot 10 units high
            aspect=2
            ) \
            .set( \
                 xlabel= 'Day Name', \
                 ylabel= 'Average Number of BikeShares', \
                 title = 'Average BikeShares - Hourly')

paragraphs.title: Workingday average usage
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
from pyspark.sql.functions import when

df_stg_dataset = df_dataset.select("workingday", "cnt") \
          .groupBy("workingday") \
          .agg({ '*' : 'count', 'cnt' : 'avg' }) \
          .toDF("workingday", "avg_shares", "num_rec")

pd_avg_shares_workingday = df_stg_dataset.withColumn("day_type", when(df_stg_dataset.workingday == 1, "weekday").otherwise("weekend") ) \
          .select('day_type', 'avg_shares') \
          .toPandas()

pd_avg_shares_workingday.head()

%spark.pyspark
sns.catplot(data=pd_avg_shares_workingday, x="day_type", y="avg_shares", 
            kind="bar",             # Options are: “point”, “bar”, “strip”, “swarm”, “box”, “violin”, or “boxen”
            palette="ch:.25",  
            height=5,              # Make the plot 10 units high
            aspect=2
            ) \
            .set( \
                 xlabel= 'Day Type', \
                 ylabel= 'Average Number of BikeShares', \
                 title = 'Average BikeShares - Day Type')

paragraphs.title: Holiday average usage
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
pd_avg_shares_holiday = df_dataset.select('holiday', 'cnt') \
          .withColumn('is_holiday', when(df_dataset.holiday == 1, 'holiday').otherwise('non holiday')) \
          .groupBy('is_holiday') \
          .agg({ 'cnt' : 'avg'  }) \
          .toDF('is_holiday', 'avg_bikeshares') \
          .toPandas()

pd_avg_shares_holiday.head()

%spark.pyspark
sns.catplot(data=pd_avg_shares_holiday, x="is_holiday", y="avg_bikeshares", 
            kind="bar",             # Options are: “point”, “bar”, “strip”, “swarm”, “box”, “violin”, or “boxen”
            palette="ch:.25",  
            height=5,              # Make the plot 10 units high
            aspect=2
            ) \
            .set( \
                 xlabel= 'Day Type', \
                 ylabel= 'Average Number of BikeShares', \
                 title = 'Average BikeShares - Holiday')

paragraphs.title: Average usage per season
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
pd_avg_shares_season = df_dataset.select('season', 'cnt') \
          .withColumn('season_name', when(df_dataset.season == 1, 'winter')
                                     .when(df_dataset.season == 2, 'spring')
                                     .when(df_dataset.season == 3, 'summer')
                                     .otherwise('fall') ) \
          .groupBy('season', 'season_name') \
          .agg({ 'cnt' : 'avg'}) \
          .orderBy('season') \
          .toDF('season', 'season_name', 'avg_bikeshares') \
          .select('season_name', 'avg_bikeshares') \
          .toPandas()

pd_avg_shares_season.head()

%spark.pyspark
sns.catplot(data=pd_avg_shares_season, x="season_name", y="avg_bikeshares", 
            kind="bar",             # Options are: “point”, “bar”, “strip”, “swarm”, “box”, “violin”, or “boxen”
            palette="ch:.25",  
            height=5,              # Make the plot 10 units high
            aspect=2
            ) \
            .set( \
                 xlabel= 'Season', \
                 ylabel= 'Average Number of BikeShares', \
                 title = 'Average BikeShares - Season')

paragraphs.title: Daily usage in 2011
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
pd_avg_shares_daily = df_dataset.withColumn('date_trx', date_format(df_dataset.dteday, 'YYYY-MM-dd')) \
          .select('date_trx' , 'cnt' ) \
          .groupBy('date_trx') \
          .agg({ 'cnt' : 'sum' }) \
          .orderBy('date_trx') \
          .toDF('date_trx', 'total_shares') \
          .toPandas()

pd_avg_shares_daily

%spark.pyspark
## it takes long time
g = sns.relplot(data=pd_avg_shares_daily, x="date_trx", y="total_shares", 
            kind="line",             # Options are: “point”, “bar”, “strip”, “swarm”, “box”, “violin”, or “boxen”
            palette="ch:.25",  
            height=5,              # Make the plot 10 units high
            aspect=5,
            )
g.set( \
      xlabel= 'Season', \
      ylabel= 'Average Number of BikeShares', \
      title = 'Average BikeShares - Season', \
      )
g.fig.autofmt_xdate()

paragraphs.title: Average usage per weather condition
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
#Bikeshares by Weather condition

# "weather_code" category description:
# 1 = Clear ; mostly clear but have some values with haze/fog/patches of fog/ fog in vicinity
# 2 = scattered clouds / few clouds
# 3 = Broken clouds
# 4 = Cloudy
# 7 = Rain/ light Rain shower/ Light rain
# 10 = rain with thunderstorm
# 26 = snowfall
# 94 = Freezing Fog

%spark.pyspark
pd_agg_shares_weather = df_dataset.groupBy('weathersit') \
          .agg({ 'cnt' : 'avg' }) \
          .orderBy('weathersit') \
          .toDF('weathersit', 'avg_shares') \
          .toPandas()

pd_agg_shares_weather

%spark.pyspark
g = sns.catplot(data=pd_agg_shares_weather, x="weathersit", y="avg_shares", 
            kind="bar",             # Options are: “point”, “bar”, “strip”, “swarm”, “box”, “violin”, or “boxen”
            palette="ch:.25",  
            height=5,              # Make the plot 10 units high
            aspect=2,
            )
g.set( \
      xlabel= 'Weather Situation', \
      ylabel= 'Average Number of BikeShares', \
      title = 'Average BikeShares - Weather Situation', \
      )

paragraphs.title: Usage relation between day and hour
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
pd_day_vs_hour_mean = df_dataset.groupBy("weekday").pivot("hr").sum("cnt").orderBy('weekday').toPandas()
pd_day_vs_hour_mean

%spark.pyspark
plt.figure(figsize=(25,5))
g = sns.heatmap(data=pd_day_vs_hour_mean, cmap="BuGn", annot=True, linewidths=.5, fmt=".1f" )
plt.xlabel("Day Hours")
plt.ylabel("Avg. Number of BikeShares ")
#plt.xticks(rotation=90,ha='right')
plt.title("Bikeshares by weekday and day hours")
